Drop ${python3:Depends} from p4lang-pi binary Depends.

The upstream debian/control uses ${python3:Depends}, which dh_python3
expands to hard runtime dependencies on python3-protobuf and
python3-grpcio. SONiC's trixie slave image deliberately omits those
apt packages because they shadow the pip-installed protobuf 5.x and
grpcio 1.71 at /usr/local (commit c5e058b88), which broke sonic-ycabled
tests. dpkg -i then fails to configure p4lang-pi during the
*-install step in slave.mk.

p4lang-pi's C++ libraries (libpi*) are what SONiC consumes; any Python
bits in the package will resolve against the pip-installed protobuf
and grpcio.

Index: p4lang-pi-0.1.0/debian/control
===================================================================
--- p4lang-pi-0.1.0.orig/debian/control
+++ p4lang-pi-0.1.0/debian/control
@@ -36,7 +36,6 @@ Architecture: any
 Depends:
     ${shlibs:Depends},
     ${misc:Depends},
-    ${python3:Depends},
     libboost1.83-dev,
     libboost-system1.83-dev,
     libboost-thread1.83-dev,

